 is 
\begin_inset Formula $m\times n$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A}$
\end_inset

 does not depend on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}$
\end_inset

.
 Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}$
\end_inset

 is a function of the vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{z}$
\end_inset

, while 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A}$
\end_inset

 is independent of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{z}$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial\mathbf{y}}{\partial\mathbf{z}}=\mathbf{A}\frac{\partial\mathbf{x}}{\partial\mathbf{z}}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Since 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
y_{i}=\sum_{k=1}^{n}a_{ik}x_{k}
\]

\end_inset

then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial y_{i}}{\partial z_{j}}=\sum_{k=1}^{n}a_{ik}\frac{\partial x_{k}}{\partial z_{j}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

